[[Image:Wensleydale cheese 2.jpg|right|thumb|Wensleydale cheese]]

'''Wensleydale''' is a white, crumbly-textured cows milk cheese, originally from Wensleydale in Yorkshire, England. Very pleasant as a dessert cheese, it has a fresh, slightly sweet taste.

Blue Wensleydale is a rarer variety; some ewes milk is added to encourage the development of blue veins. 

